When leftists attempt to critique so-called "AI art", they just point at some minor defect like a malformed finger or an extra tooth, that will obviously be patched out in a few months. They are fundamentally unable to present a serious critique that gets to the actual substance.

E.g. that image of "What would it look like if the Roman Empire existed in 2023" is a worse indictment than any polydactylism (a mistake fallen Nature also makes!), because it's like the definition of platitude. It's the one thing the Roman empire today would look like the least.

An input of "what if Otto Bismarck was a corporate CEO" would produce exactly what you imagine. But this is not what Bismarck would be as a corporate CEO. It would be something completely different and unrecognizable that surprises you. An-anti platitude algorithm is an oxymoron.
